To style a checkbox using light purple, you can use CSS. Here's an example of how you can achieve this:

```css:mocked/enhanced_context/styles.css
/* Style the checkbox */
input[type="checkbox"] {
    accent-color: lightpurple;
}

/* For browsers that do not support accent-color */
input[type="checkbox"] {
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    background-color: lightpurple;
    border: 2px solid #ccc;
    border-radius: 3px;
    appearance: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    -moz-appearance: none;
    outline: none;
    cursor: pointer;
}

input[type="checkbox"]:checked {
    background-color: lightpurple;
    border: 2px solid lightpurple;
    position: relative;
}

input[type="checkbox"]:checked::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 2px;
    left: 6px;
    width: 6px;
    height: 12px;
    border: solid white;
    border-width: 0 2px 2px 0;
    transform: rotate(45deg);
}
```

This CSS will style the checkbox with a light purple color. The `accent-color` property is used for browsers that support it, and additional styles are provided for browsers that do not support `accent-color`.

